Crambus silvella is a species of moth of the family Crambidae. It is found in Europe.
The wingspan is 22–26 millimetres (0.87–1.02 in). Differs from Crambus pascuella as follows : forewings with apex little produced, dorsum less whitish, median streak less broad, continued beyond second line to termen, costal spot before second line much more elongate.The moth flies from July to September depending on the location.
The larvae feed on Carex species.